com.salesforce.omakase.plugin

Interface Plugin

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DependentPlugin, GrammarPlugin, ParserPlugin, PostProcessingPlugin
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AutoRefine, BasePlugin, Conditionals, ConditionalsCollector, ConditionalsRefiner, ConditionalsValidator, DeclarationPlugin, DirectionFlipPlugin, FontFacePlugin, KeyframesPlugin, LinearGradientPlugin, MediaPlugin, PrefixCleaner, Prefixer, PseudoElementValidator, SelectorPlugin, StandardValidation, StyleWriter, SupportsPlugin, SyntaxTree, UnquotedIEFilterPlugin, UrlPlugin

    public interface Plugin
    A plugin that is registered during CSS processing to perform refinement, rework, validation, and more.

    Plugins are registered during parser setup using Omakase.Request.use(Plugin...) (and similar methods). Plugins will generally be executed in the order that they are registered.

    Note that when implementing a plugin, not all subscriptions will be received automatically. sometimes refinement, such as with AutoRefine, is necessary. See the main readme file for more information.

    Subscription method invocation order follows this pattern:

    @Refine -> @Rework / @Observe -> @Validate.

    In a class hierarchy, the more specific type is received before the more abstract type (e.g., ClassSelector subscription methods invoked before Selector subscription methods).

    For much more information on utilizing or creating plugins please see the main readme file.
